<HEAD>Matsushita Sends $1 Million to San Francisco</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Matsushita Electric Industrial Co., Ltd. has
donated $1 million to the city of San Francisco to help victims of
the earthquake that rocked the Bay area last week, company
officials said today.
   Matsushita President Akio Tanii presented the U.S. consul
general in Osaka, Gregory L. Johnson, with a $1 million check, said
Akio Nagano, a company spokesman.
   Johnson will forward the check to Gov. George Deukmejian of
California, the spokesman said.
   Several other Japanese companies and even regional governments
have sent aid to San Francisco. Sumitomo Bank donated $500,000,
Tokyo prefecture $15,000 and the city of Osaka, Japan's second
largest, $10,000.
