<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 79-20 roll call by which the
Senate on Thursday approved the death penalty as punishment for
terrorists who kill Americans overseas.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to impose the death penalty
while a no vote was a vote against it.
   Voting yes were 40 Democrats and 39 Republicans.
   Voting no were 15 Democrats and 5 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
   Adams, D-Wash., yes; Armstrong, R-Colo., yes; Baucus, D-Mont.,
yes; Bentsen, D-Texas, yes; Biden, D-Del., yes.
   Bingaman, D-N.M., yes; Bond, R-Mo., yes; Boren, D-Okla., yes;
