<FIRST>u i AM-Venezuela-Bomb     10-26 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Venezuela-Bomb,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Guardsmen Killed by Bomb on Venezuela-Colombia Border</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN CRISTOBAL, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five national guardsmen on
patrol along the border with Colombia were killed Thursday when a
bomb exploded under their truck, military spokesmen said.
   No one claimed responsibility for the attack, but speculation
centered on the Colombian leftist guerrillas who operate along the
border.
   The truck carrying the five was on its way early Thursday from
El Nula to Cutufi, two towns several miles apart in Apure state
about 400 miles southwest of Caracas, said Gen. Rafael Caballero,
national guard commander in the region.
   A charge of dynamite was set off, killing all five aboard, he
said.
   Venezuelan and Colombian military authorities say leftist
Colombian guerrillas operate on both sides of the border.
Venezuelan forces have been beefed up in recent months following
the Colombian government's mid-August crackdown on suspected drug
traffickers.
</TEXT>
