<HEAD>Members of Congress Demand Castro Release Political Prisoners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 50 members of Congress signed a
letter to Cuban President Fidel Castro demanding that he free three
human rights activists.
   The letter, circulated by Reps. Robert Torricelli, D-N.J., and
Silvio Conte, R-Mass., was made public Wednesday and asked that
