<HEAD>London Stocks Fall Sharply on Bad Earnings News</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates with sharp drop on poor ICI results</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chemicals giant ICI showed lower-than-expected
third-quarter profits Thursday, prompting a sharp drop in London
stock prices on a market already weakened by fears of a British
recession.
   Imperial Chemical Industries PLC reported an 8 percent increase
in profits for the nine months to Sept. 30 to 1.23 million pounds,
or $1.98 million, but the third-quarter profit was down 41 million
pounds to 306 million pounds, well below market forecasts.
   ICI shares fell 55 pence to 11.15 pounds.
   The market fell sharply before recovering somewhat. In late
afternoon, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was
down 18.1 points, or 0.8 percent, at 2,143.8 points.
   ``No one is interested in buying. I have hardly done any deals
at all this morning,'' one trader said before the ICI-driven fall.
   Another dealer said recent gyrations in world equity markets,
combined with growing pessimism about the British economic outlook,
turned already shy investors into ``complete cowards.''
   ``The institutions just don't have any incentive to get involved
at the moment,'' one trader said. He reported selected buying of
quality blue-chips, but added, ``apart from that it's absolutely
dead.''
   Volume came to a light 271.7 million shares compared with 179.2
million shares at the same time Wednesday.
</TEXT>
