<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates throughout with closing prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices closed sharply lower Thursday after
the market's confidence in British corporate profits was shaken by
bellwether Imperial Chemical Industries PLC's disappointing
third-quarter results.
   ICI, which is a key component of the Financial Times-Stock
Exchange 100-share index, said its pre-tax profit for the quarter
dropped by 12 percent to the equivalent of $490 million,
significantly under market expectations.
   As ICI's share price fell, the 100-share index followed.
   The key index closed at its session low of 2,129.4, down 32.5
points, or 1.5 percent. It had been pressured from the outset of
dealings by expectations of soft ICI earnings.
   ``ICI is a bellwether of U.K. corporate profitability,'' a
senior dealer with Warburg Securities said. ``It's results were
disappointing. The market followed.''
   ICI finished 73 pence lower at 10.97 pounds.
   The Financial Times 30-share index fell 31.4 points to close at
1,720.5. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 17.01 points to
close at 1,183.39.
   Volume came to 443.6 million shares, compared with 374.6 million
shares on Wednesday.
