<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
217,421 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
212,637, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 250,592 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 146,971 cars this week,
compared with 143,497 a week ago and 162,323 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 70,450,
compared with last week's 69,140 and last year's 88,179.
   Canadian automakers were to build 26,256 cars this week, up from
23,436 a week ago and up from last year's 22,463.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,288,
compared with 20,903 a week ago and 21,841 in the same week last
year.
